<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>do you want a bet • you bet</xh5><p> <i>do you want a bet—</i>an emphatic way of saying that what has been stated is wrong: “You’ll wind up in the hospital,” Claude said. “<u>Do you want a bet</u>?”</p><p> <i>you bet</i>—(also: I bet) an emphatic way of saying “certainly,” “of course”: “Can you handle this outfit?” “<u>You bet</u>,” said the scout.</p> </entry>
